      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 113: The observer now buffers every auth event while tempAccount is nil. If unrelated accounts emit auth callbacks before createTemporaryAccount() completes or if account creation hangs/fails, pendingAuthResults can grow without bound and retain stale events across the view model lifetime. Filter to only states relevant to temporary account linking, or cap/clear the buffer on failure/cancellation. For example:\n```suggestion\naccountsService.authStateSubject\n    .filter { result in result.state \u003d\u003d .tokenAvailable || result.state \u003d\u003d .connecting || result.state \u003d\u003d .done || result.state \u003d\u003d .error }\n    .observe(on: MainScheduler.instance)\n```\nAlso clear pendingAuthResults in the cancellation/failure path before setting the error state.",
